From: Limeng <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
Date: Fri, 18 Mar 2016 14:15:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] usb: gadget: f_rndis: fix a memory leak issue

when remove module usb_f_rndis.ko, rndis_free_inst() function
is called to free memory allocated in rndis_alloc_inst(). Original
code passes opts->rndis_os_desc.group.default_groups to kfree(),
but it should be opts->func_inst.group.default_groups. Because
opts->func_inst.group is the first parameter of function
usb_os_desc_prepare_interf_dir() that allocates memory pointed
by opts->func_inst.group.default_groups.

Signed-off-by: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/usb/gadget/function/f_rndis.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/gadget/function/f_rndis.c b/drivers/usb/gadget/function/f_rndis.c
index 829edf8..d42e661 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/gadget/function/f_rndis.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/gadget/function/f_rndis.c
@@ -903,7 +903,7 @@ static void rndis_free_inst(struct usb_function_instance *f)
 			free_netdev(opts->net);
 	}
 
-	kfree(opts->rndis_os_desc.group.default_groups); /* single VLA chunk */
+	kfree(opts->func_inst.group.default_groups); /* single VLA chunk */
 	kfree(opts);
 }
 
